analysis: The documents are all executive orders signed by President Harry S. Truman. They cover a range of topics, including foreign service appointments, amendments to previous executive orders, control of the Panama Canal, housing provisions related to national defense, income tax laws in Guam, foreign aid, the Coast Guard's operational status, the US High Commissioner for Germany, the Advisory Board on Just Compensation, and the Economic Cooperation Act. Many of the documents amend or revoke previous executive orders or delegate authority to specific individuals or departments.
title: Truman Era Government and Policy Adjustments
